  "text": "We consider a LBS system on mobile cloud involving three different entities [CITATION_1] as illustrated in Figure 1 . We assume that Certification Center is a trusted third party (TTP), in which the user ID is omitted from the location query and the network address of the query message is anonymized through sender anonymity mechanisms such as Crowds or Onion Routing. Mobile User is an entity who wants to access LBS data. It is issued with a service certificate with certain access privileges. A user can access its current location information either by a equipped GPS device or through a location information provider.",
